'''polysaccharide''' (''plural'' '''polysaccharides''')
#{{Chemistry}} A [[polymer]] made of many [[saccharide]] units linked by [[ether]] [[bond]]s.
#{{Biochemistry}} [[Cellulose]], [[starch]]es, and complex [[carbohydrate]]s, such as [[glycogen]], are [[common]] polysaccharides in [[biology]].
